author: Andrew T. Bradley
title: Affordable earbuds that sound great!

$300 for Fruity Earpods!?  Are you kidding me!?  Those guys over at Fruity think they could sell anything and mark up the price 1000%.

But seriously, don't waste your money.  Buy these earbuds.  They sync up easily to whatever bluetooth device, and they sound great.  No ear pain after having them in for hours.  They don't fall out.  Easy to use, easy to charge.  They just work great!

author: Kom
title: Amazing earbuds at very affordable price. Love them!
content:
I have been in market for true wireless earbuds for a week now. Having looked at many options on Amazon, I decided to purchase this ones based on 100% customer satisfaction reviews. At first I was hesitant as I was not sure what to expect from this headphones primarily because they are not noise cancelling. For the price point though, I decided to give this one's a try. After using it for a week now, I love this earbuds.

Package was delivered on time and headphone are packed in premium feeling box. Once opened you are greeted with charging box and two earphones. They came fully charged and likewise the charging case. Pairing was easy, turned bluetooth on and they were ready to set up with my Pixel 2 XL. Headphones automatically turn on once you remove them from case and they pair with my phone and other headphones right away. Once you are done using it pop it back in the case and they get charged for next time use. Audio quality is acceptable for headphone priced so reasonably. I have a little hard time keeping them in my ear but once adjusted, they seem to stay in. Noise cancellation is my only concern with this headphones, I have to keep them loud for best experience. I love it when it auto pause and play based on headphone position within ear.

Recommendation- I like this headphones and definitely recommend them for purchase. If you are in market for wireless earbuds, consider this ones. You won't be disappointed.

author: Falon
title: Just like apple airpods. The price is phenomenal for the quality.
content: My son is raving about these. He has been begging for wireless earbuds for a while now but we could not afford them. These are so affordable first off. They arrived promptly and were easy to remove from box. We charged them up for about 2 hours. Me and my son both tried them and they are very comfortable inside the ear. No pain or uncomfortable sensation. They stay put which is great. The sound quality is wonderful with these earbuds. The volume can be easy controlled. Phone calls easily answered. I have one happy kid over here.

author: Scott J. Ducey
title: Bad Experience
content:
Maybe I am an outlier here, as it seems that people like the product overall (based on reviews). I feel I may have received a real crappy pair. Two days after I purchased, the panel on one of the buds came off exposing the the electronics inside.  I would also say, the short time I wore the buds, they were not comfortable to wear. Also when I used it for making phone calls, people on the other end would say things like "whats wrong with your phone, you sound like you are far away / in a tunnel / poor reception". I attempted to glue the panel back on, but that ended up being a disaster, so I just through out the product.  My son has the buds from APPLE. I used them for two days, and I did not have the same complaints on phone calls, and they seemed comfortable.

I am not trying to trash the product, but that was my experience. Given how inexpensive they are, they might be good for you. Hope this helps.

author: Wendy C
title: Good quality at an inexpensive price
content: This review will be based on the price to be fair.  I have used alot of headphones over the years.  From studio sony headphones for music production to 1980's walkman headphones.  First I'll start with build quality.  These feel really nice.  They fit nicely into the charger and are magnetized to keep them in there.  The build quality it juat as good as the airports.  Connecting was easy.  When they are not connected to a device they are automatically in pair mode when they are in the charging case, which charges without being plugged in....awesome.  Once I found them in my Bluetooth settings on my phone they were ready to go.  Didn't have to even turn them on.  Just put them in my ears and ready.  They fit comfortably and seemed to stay in place.  Started spotify and tested with music.  They aren't noise canceling though.  I like my music a little on the loud side and these seemed to be a little quiet.  After listening for a while I am sure I would adjust.  Now for the audio quality.....the meat and potatos.  Bass was surprisingly present and not muddy, like alot of inexpensive ones.  The mids were ok but lacking on the high end.  Time to EQ them via phone audio settings.  I pretty much had to turn the mids and highs way up to get the desired sound.  I wasn't able to get them as crisp sounding as I wanted but it was adequate for the price point and still will be easily usable.  Haven't tested the charge time yet but it isn't supposed to last long anyway.  Are these for you?  The build quality and fit shouldn't disappoint.  If you don't require your headphones to be the best sounding you can find then these should be good.  If that's what you want, and can afford it, spend the $100 plus...  Easy to use with phone calls as well.  Technology has allowed better products at a much more reasonable price than it did several years ago.

author: Lincoln Cao
title: Super comfortable, and BETTER value than Apple version
content:
I absolutely love these Earbuds.  I spend alot of time driving in traffic and usually listen to my wired headphones, but the problem is, sometimes when I turn my head, the headphones get ripped off my phone.
These earbuds solve this problem.
I can listen to my audiobooks with no problems, with no worries of it falling off or damaging my phone.
Also, when I am driving and have my GPS to navigate, I can hear the directions clearly in my ear while I am listening to my radio and safely keep both my hands on the wheel.
I was concerned about comfort at first, but these earbuds are very light and comfortable, sometimes you forget that you still have them on.  I have been using them for 3 days, about 4 hours daily, and I still do not need to charge it yet.  Very long lasting battery, and I would highly recommend this as a Christmas gift.

author: Shabbir
title: Airpod-like Feel at a Fraction of the Price..!
content:
This is just a good pair of earbuds. Period. What do people seek in earbuds?
Good sound quality - check
Solid build quality - check
Fairly good battery life - check
The convenience of wireless - check
Easy connectivity - check
Elegant and good looks - check
And finally, price - check check check! You can't beat 'em at this price.

I am not a technology fanatic. I always believed in wired earphones because of the benefits it offered. These are my first wireless earbuds and I have got to say I am very impressed. This product has opened my eyes to the convenience of wireless tech. Very happy with this purchase. And the seller is great. No complaints from my side.
The only feedback I would have for the manufacturer is to consider a USB - C type charging port. But it is no way a deal breaker for me! 5-stars from my side.

So when I connected it to my phone last night, my wife was asleep and I didn't want to make any noise being afraid I could wake her up. So I played an episode of a TV show on my phone on my YouTube app and my first reaction was to look around hastily because I thought the sound was coming from outside. It blew my mind! I love it!
Also, I should mention the great case design that holds the earbuds in magnetically. I am very pleased with this product :)

content: I bought a set of these for my fiance as they kind of look like the airpods by apple and she is an apple product user but not willing to spend that kind of money. The earbuds give a signal when the charge on the bud itself is low but you get a solid 7 hours out of them. Recharge time is about 2 hours or so. When they are low just sit them in the case and theyll recharge themselves. The sound quality is solid and I cant tell the difference between by Dads bose earbuds and these other than maybe Bose has a little better noise cancelling ability and a little more base. For the money you cant beat these at all.

author: castorandpollux
title: Great set of headphones at a low price point!
content:
Being an Android user, I was on the lookout for a good pair of Bluetooth ear pods that wouldn’t cost me a fortune. Having tried several sets of similarly priced headphones (both Bluetooth/wired) in the past, I didn’t have very high expectations from these as far as sound quality, and ease of use. However, I must confess I was blown away by how good these were at the $30 price point!

Pros:
1. Crystal clear sound – no background static/tinny output
2. Pods pair automatically when taken out of the case
3. Good mic quality – had no complaints from people at the other end when using these to attend phone calls
4. Very good battery life (based on one week of usage)

Cons:
1. Pods do not have silicone tips, hence no noise isolation
2. Again, due to the lack of silicone tips, they may feel a little loose (fitment-wise)
3. Switching back and forth between songs requires use of buttons on both pods

Overall – I would certainly recommend these if you are in the market for a pair of new pods!

Disclaimer: I received a complimentary set for an honest review on Amazon.

content:

Another good thing is turning them on/off is easy, just remove them from the charging case and they turn on and put them back to turn them off, its simple. And like most of the earphones out there, they connect to the last device you used them with, but its easy to switch device.
You have the flexibility to just use one piece, if you like and sometimes it does come handy. Another function I like is the automatic ear detection, just remove a piece from you ear and playback will pause and resume once you put it back, this does help when someone drops by for a conversation and you don't need to actually pickup your phone to pause the playback.
The battery life is definitely impressive,  And it's easy to carry everywhere, it being so small.

content: Arrived super fast. Packaged very well.  Impressed with the overall look

author: Mandy
title: Great sound, great quality!
content: I travel a lot and these things are a life saver. They are great quality and the sounds is awesome.  I compared then to me husband's very expensive brand and mine sounds just as good if not better. I recommend these! I love how they charge while ib the protective case too

author: Aaron
title: Great product
content: These head phones are great, they are very comfortable and durable. They have great sound quality, and connect easily to Bluetooth. Most wireless buds that I have used tend to cut out once one has been placed in the case but these continue to stay connected. Overall, these are well worth the money!

author: Rob Claro
title: Worth the price. Dont settle for pricey airpods, get this as alternative
content: I just broke my airpods and i didnt want to spend anothet $100.00+ for some so i searched for alternative and im glad i found this one. This has clear sound quality and it functions perfect just like my old airpods.

author: E&J
title: Great purchase
content: Husband likes these. They look like the new Apple EarPods, sound great too. He uses them for the gym and likes these better than the round bulkier ones.

author: Kevin
title: New tech is great
content: I finally upgraded from the old wireless earbuds and these new features makes life so much more convenient. I like how they automatically turn on and pair to your phone the moment you take them out of the case, along with the opposite. I don't have to scramble around looking for the darn small power button like my old ones. These are a great cheaper alternative than the Airpods, just with some less features such as wireless charging that I don't really need anyways nor do I want to pay an extra hundred for. I compared these to my friend's Airpods, and I couldn't tell much of a difference in sound quality, but then again I'm not that of an audiophile.

author: zone
title: Good wireless headphones
content: Got this headphones for my son, who lost his more expensive model.  After using it for a couple hours, he claimed that he did not see much of a difference from his previous one.  They are pretty comfortable and stable in his hears , and did not lack the quality of the sound.  I am happy he likes this, and it won't hurt as much, if they were to get lost, as the tag was not as big.

author: Payal Layla
title: Wireless much easy
content: This wireless earbuds are very useful for me since I am taking many phone calls in a day. This has good sound quality. there is different light system to indicate battery level and and connectivity. Also button works for to hang up the call. Also get charged fast and stay on for like day or day and half.

author: lee
title: Love them ty
content: Just like airpods  my daughter loves them. She shows them off as airpods lol

author: C. Teh
title: Fits super well with the right amount of bass!!
content: I was not sure how good this would be. Well, pleasantly surprised how comfortable it sits in the ear when listening and how stable and secure it was. It fits really well and the sound is great with just the right amount of bass. Pairing was a breeze with my iPhone. I think because it is naturally sitting in the ear well and not having to be held in, I do not feel any strain or pain around the ear. This is a keeper!!

author: Kelly M
title: Cute and comfortable!
content: These headphones look very similar to the Apple Airpods. They are comfortable in the ears and sound great. I tried putting them in the case while still playing music on my phone and when the second headphone went into the case it paused the music on my phone as it should. The only thing I thought was weird was when I tried to listen to something on my phone later on without the headphones it wouldn’t play through the phone speaker because it was still connected to the headphones in the case. Not sure if this is common or if you are supposed to disconnect when not using them.

author: Aakash Varshney
title: Good Sound Quality
content: I really like the sound quality which is crisp and it connects instantly as soon as you open the case. I am really satisfied with the product and would definitely recommend you to buy it.

author: Mark Stewart
title: Bluetooth Wireless Earbuds
content: I was really impressed at how they can pack in such good sounding audio into these little earbuds. They felt nice and solid too!
